CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, National edition, July 11, 1942, pg. 14, reads: "Pittsburghers Hail Fighting Men from New York's 372nd Infantry and Fort Riley's Ninth Calvary - Pittsburgh was full of military spirit over the holidays when members of two famous colored units of the United States Army participated in colorful displays of military routine. Top left: The colors pass by, in impressive parade of the 372nd Infantry as they marched up Fifth Avenue near Wylie Saturday... Harris [illegible] photos."
TitMainTitle: Four color guard from 372nd Infantry marching in front of soldiers in parade, Fifth Avenue, Downtown
